The Man. The Myth. The 40-Year-Old.
"I want bands,
I want a rave,
I want everyone I love
in one filthy field
in Wales."

So that's what we're doing. Three days at Three Pools — a world-class permaculture farm in the foothills of the Black Mountains. Bands from 2pm Saturday, rave in the barn 10pm–4am. Sauna. Farm food. Proper bar. £90 a head covers the costs. No profit. Just Phil's birthday.

I'm In — Get a Ticket
★ Three Pools Permaculture Farm · Near Abergavenny, Wales

The Venue

141 acres in the foothills of the Black Mountains. Renovated barns, a Void soundsystem install, three indoor dancefloors, a d&b PA for the stage, sauna, licensed bar, kitchen, camping fields, and eco cabins. This is not a field in a car park.

Saturday 3rd October 2026

★ Where You'll Sleep

Camping + Sleep

Three Pools has proper camping facilities — not a festival mudpit. Everyone stays on site. Hot showers and clean toilets. Bring a good sleeping bag: October nights in the Black Mountains are cold.

⛺
Camping Fields (Included in Ticket)

Flat grass pitches, fire pits, hot showers, and proper toilets. Bring your tent and a solid sleeping bag.

🚐
Live-In Vehicles Welcome

Space on site for campervans and motorhomes. Register your vehicle with Phil when you buy your ticket.

🔔
6 Glamping Bell Tents — Book Direct

Only 6 bell tents available at Three Pools. Pre-pitched, beds and bedding included. Book directly with the venue at threepools.co.uk — these will go fast.

🏠
Eco Cabins — Book Direct

Handmade eco cabins sleeping 2–4, built from locally-sourced materials. Check availability at threepools.co.uk.

💧
Sauna

On-site sauna. Available Saturday and Sunday mornings. Essential.

Good to know
Pack for cold nights

October in the Black Mountains. Bring layers. The rave barn will be warm, the walk back at 4am will not.

No day visitors

Everyone stays on site for the full weekend. It keeps the headcount right and the vibe right.

Kids & dogs welcome

The farm is stunning — lots of space for little ones and dogs during the day. Have a chat with Phil about the night situation.

Book Glamping at Three Pools ↗
★ Farm to Plate

Food + Drink

Three Pools grows its own food on site — fresh farm produce sold throughout the weekend. Self-catering is totally welcome, and BYOB is allowed back at the campsite.

🌿
Farm-Grown Food on Site

Fresh produce grown right here on the farm. Honest, seasonal food throughout the weekend.

🍳
Self-Catering Welcome

Bring your camping stove. Cook your own. The more the merrier around the campfire.

🎂
Saturday Birthday Lunch

Everyone together on Saturday before the bands kick off. Farm food on site.

🍺
Bar: Nice Ales, Beer & Cider

A proper bar with good choices. Open from Friday afternoon, through Saturday, and into the rave barn overnight.

🏕
BYOB in the Campsite

Bring your own to the tent. No glass in the venue. You know the drill.

🌙
Late Bar in the Rave Barn

Bar open all night inside the barn. Water always available — look after yourself and each other.
